revision.text:
{{Infobox meteorite |Name= Adelie Land |Image= |Image_caption= |Type= Chondrite |Class= [[Ordinary chondrite]] |Group= L6<ref name=database /> |Structural_classification= |Composition= |Shock= |Weathering= |Country= [[Antarctica]] |Region= [[Adélie Land]] |Lat_Long= {{coord|67|11|S|142|23|E|region:AQ|display=inline,title}}<ref name=database>{{metbull|378|Adelie Land}}</ref> |Observed_fall= No |Fall_date= |Found_date= 1912 |TKW= 1000 g<ref name=database /> |Image2= |Image2_caption= }} '''Adelie Land'''<ref name=database /> is a [[meteorite]] discovered on December 5, 1912, in [[Antarctica]] by [[Francis Howard Bickerton]] (1889-1954), a member of Sir [[Douglas Mawson]]'s Australasian Antarctic Expedition. It was named after [[Adélie Land]] and it was the first meteorite found in Antarctica.<ref>{{cite book |title= Home of the Blizzard|last=Mawson |first=Douglas |year=1996 |publisher=Wakefield Press |location=Kent Town S.A. 5067 |isbn=978 1 86254 876 3 |page=}}</ref>
Only one fragment of about {{convert|1|kg}} was found. It was classified as L5 [[ordinary chondrite]].
