{{Infobox football club | clubname = Ayat Stars | fullname = Ayat Stars Football Club | image = | nickname = The Thunders | founded = {{Start date and years ago|df=yes|2009|12|30}} | ground = [[Aweil Stadium]] | capacity = 1,500 | chrtitle = President | chairman = Steigner Ramatalli | mgrtitle = Head Coach | manager = Deng Atak | league = [[South Sudan Premier League]] | season = [[South Sudan Premier League|SSPL 2015]] | position = '''27th''' place | current = 2016 South Sudan Premier League | website = http://www.ayatstarsfc.com | pattern_la1=_blue_adidas_houlders|pattern_b1=|pattern_ra1=_blue_adidas_shoulders| | leftarm1=FF0000|body1=FF0000|rightarm1=FF0000|shorts1=FF0000|socks1=FF0000| | pattern_la2=_white_adidas_houlders|pattern_b2=|pattern_ra2=_white_adidas_houlders| | leftarm2=FF8000|body2=FF8000|rightarm2=FF8000|shorts2=FF8000|socks2=FF8000 }} '''Ayat Stars Football Club''', also known as '''Ayat Stars''' or simply '''Ayat''', is a [[South Sudanese]] soccer club. The club is currently based in Aweil Centre County, [[Aweil State]], in northwestern South Sudan, near the International border with the Republic of Sudan and the Abyei Region.<ref>The coordinates of Aweil are: 8° 46' 02.00"N, 27° 23' 59.00"E (Latitude: 8.7671; Longitude: 27.3998).</ref> The team is nicknamed "The Thunders". It was formed on December 30, 2009, and initially started as a part of the [[South Sudan Premier League|South Sudan Premier League (SSPL)]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gurtong.net/ECM/Editorial/tabid/124/ctl/ArticleView/mid/519/articleId/16614/El-Salam-FC-Thrashed-2-1-By-Ayat-Stars-FC.aspx/|title=El Salam FC Thrashed 2-1 By Ayat Stars FC > Gurtong Trust > Editorial|first=Gurtong|last=Trust|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eyeradio.org/aweil-1st-division-league-continues/|title=Aweil 1st division league continues|date=30 April 2015|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://radiotamazuj.org/en/article/al-salam-wins-2-1-against-al-marreikh-aweil/ |title=Al-Salam wins 2-1 against Al-Marreikh in Aweil - Radio Tamazuj |publisher= |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151120002537/https://radiotamazuj.org/en/article/al-salam-wins-2-1-against-al-marreikh-aweil/ |archivedate=2015-11-20 }}</ref> Ayat shares [[Aweil Stadium]] with various teams such as [[Tuektuek F.C.|Tuektuek]], [[Madiria F.C.|Madiria]], [[Apada F.C.|Apada]], [[Merreikh Aweil]], [[Salaam Aweil FC|Salaam Aweil]] and [[Aweil Stars F.C.|Aweil Stars]]. They participate in the [[South Sudan Premier League]], [[South Sudan National Cup]] and [[South Sudan Football Championship]], depending on qualification.
==Club history== Ayat Stars beat Salaam Aweil on May 6th, 2015, at 2-1.
