The '''High Commission of Cameroon''' in [[London]] is the [[diplomatic mission]] of [[Cameroon]] in the [[United Kingdom]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/263519/LDL_December_2013.pdf |title=The London Diplomatic List |date=13 December 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131211155353/https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/263519/LDL_December_2013.pdf |archivedate=11 December 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>

A protest was held outside the embassy in 2013 following the murder of Cameroonian gay-rights activist Eric Lembembe. This led to several more protests in [[Cameroon]], especially in the southern regions.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://ilga.org/ilga/en/article/ocvgWua1S6 |title=London: protesters rally at Cameroon High Commission |date=24 July 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203040338/http://ilga.org/ilga/en/article/ocvgWua1S6 |archivedate=3 December 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>

