{{Infobox organization |name = Lex Mundi |motto = The Mark of Excellence |formation = 1989 |status = Association |headquarters = Houston, Texas, United States |region_served = Worldwide |membership = Independent law firms |website = [http://www.lexmundi.com Lex Mundi]
}}
'''''Lex Mundi''''' is a [[professional services networks|professional services network]]. It is the largest [[law firm network]].{{Citation needed|date=March 2018}} The network was established in 1989. As of 2015 it had over 160 member firms totaling at more than 21,000 attorneys.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lexmundi.com/lexmundi/Member_Firms.asp|title=Lex Mundi – Member Firms|work=lexmundi.com}}</ref> The network provides information to its members about developments in local and global law.
Each member firm is required to provide a full range of commercial legal services and be considered a leader in the use of technology and law firm management.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lexmundi.com/lexmundi/Premier_Member_Firms.asp|title=Lex Mundi – Premier Member Law Firms|work=lexmundi.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.farris.com/global-services/lex-mundi/|title=British Columbia's Lex Mundi Law Firm {{!}} Farris|last=admin|website=www.farris.com|access-date=2017-05-25}}</ref>
Lex Mundi's leadership consists of six Officers and a Board of Directors.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lexmundi.com/lexmundi/Officers.asp|title=Lex Mundi – Officers|work=lexmundi.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lexmundi.com/lexmundi/Board_of_Directors.asp|title=Lex Mundi – Board of Directors|work=lexmundi.com}}</ref>
The non-profit Lex Mundi Pro Bono Foundation, a Lex Mundi affiliate, coordinates member firms who offer [[pro bono]] legal services to social entrepreneurs around the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lexmundiprobono.org/|title=Lex Mundi Pro Bono Foundation – Lawyers Helping Social Entrepreneurs Change the World|work=lexmundiprobono.org}}</ref>
