{{Infobox diocese |jurisdiction = Diocese |name = Sintang |latin = Dioecesis Sintangensis |local = Keuskupan Sintang |country = [[Indonesia]] |metropolitan = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Pontianak|Pontianak]] |province = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Pontianak|Pontianak]] |rite = [[Latin Rite]] |cathedral = Cathedral of Christ the King in [[Sintang Regency]] |cocathedral = |parishes = 36 |area_km2 = 62,103 |population = 731,000 |population_as_of = 2010 |catholics = 215,551 |catholics_percent= 29.5 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = [[Samuel Oton Sidin]] OFM.Cap |metro_archbishop = [[Agustinus Agus]] (appointed June 3, 2014; formerly Bishop of Sintang)<ref>http://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/en/bollettino/pubblico/2014/06/03/0403/00914.html</ref> |coadjutor = |vicar_general = Leonardus Miau |auxiliary_bishops= |website = [http://keuskupansintang.org/ Website of the Diocese] }}
The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Sintang''' ({{lang-la| Sintangen(sis)}}) is a [[diocese]] located in the city of [[Sintang]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Pontianak|Pontianak]] in Indonesia.
==History== * March 11, 1948: Established as the [[Apostolic Prefecture]] of Sintang from the Apostolic Vicariate of Pontianak * April 23, 1956: Promoted as Apostolic Vicariate of Sintang * January 3, 1961: Promoted as Diocese of Sintang
==Leadership== * [[Bishop]]s of Sintang (Roman rite) ** Bishop Agustinus Agus (October 29, 1999 – June 3, 2014); appointed Metropolitan Archbishop of the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Pontianak]] by [[Pope Francis]] ** Fr. Agustinus Agus (later Bishop) (Apostolic Administrator 1996 – October 29, 1999) ** Bishop [[Isak Doera]] (December 9, 1976 – January 1, 1996) ** Bishop [[Lambert van Kessel]], [[Missionaries of the Company of Mary|S.M.M.]] (May 16, 1961 – May 25, 1973) * Prefects Apostolic of Sintang (Roman Rite) ** Fr. Lambert van Kessel, S.M.M. (later Bishop) (Apostolic Administrator April 23, 1956 – May 16, 1961) ** Fr. Lambert van Kessel, S.M.M. (later Bishop) (June 4, 1948 – April 23, 1956)
